Merge pull request #7 from fviard/better_error_detection

Fix error detection and lying cache issues + mount time error reporting

Exit with a mount error if no or bad device detected

Move most of the "init" step inside the "main" function.
So, errors can be reported to the user at the mount stage and the fuse
mount be canceled early enough.
In the gphotofs_init(), fuse has already forked, and the mount is
already done, so it is too late to report any error.

Before this fix, it was possible to run gphotofs and have a mount point
even if there wasn't any device detected or if the connection parameters
were not good.

In addition, the init was not perfoming any real "request" to the device
if no particular option were used. So a lack of connected device was not
even detected.
A call to getstorage is done at the init stage to check that the device
is working and that it makes sense to let fuse create the mount point.

As in "simple-mtpfs", we exit with an error if no "storage" is detected.
It is the case for example with a "nexus" device that is in "charger"
mode.

Fixes statfs when the target device has multiple storages.

Reports the total storage of all the storages of a device.
Before, if there was more than 1 storage for a device, stats was exiting
with an error.

(+memory free fix)

Detect disconnected device and avoid filetree corruption because of the cache

Use the "check_events" call to detect if the device was disconnected or
is not working anymore.
This is especially usefull for syscalls that are able to use the
gphotofs cache like getattr.
Without it, a client of the fuse can sometimes think that the device is
working but has an "empty" content or some "empty" folders when in fact
it is just that the device is in a bad state or removed.
So, this prevent a "copy" tool to report that a complete copy succeed
when it is infact not the case.

This needs the following patch of libgphoto2:
https://github.com/gphoto/libgphoto2/pull/189
(Otherwise, the behavior will be same as before)

Only call get_file on demand in the read function, if we do not have the file_read

this is work on https://github.com/gphoto/gphotofs/issues/4
